    "To provide a comprehensive comparison, we included additional Active Learning methods, namely QBC (Query by Committee), EMC (Expected Model Change), and Bayesian Generative AL.",
    "The results, as shown in Table 1, indicate that Bayesian Generative AL achieves the highest accuracy, reaching 92.75% by the eighth cycle.",
    "This method's performance is particularly notable, as it consistently outperforms QBC and EMC, demonstrating its efficacy in the CIFAR10 dataset context.",
    "Tables 3 and 4 show clear differences in performance between the different active learning methods on CIFAR100.",
    "Similarity-based selection performs worse than Random sampling at each round, with lower accuracy."
